<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="315" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1168,1338]" pageId="14" pageNumber="315">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1204,1230]" pageId="14" pageNumber="315">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae slightly longer than body; scape robust, elongate, sinuous, strongly projected at inner apex. Prothorax with prominent lateral tubercles placed medially; pronotum bituberculate. Elytra with prominent conical centrobasal crest; metatarsomere I longer than the two following together. Number of species currently included: 1.
</paragraph>
